10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Insider trading</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most of the cases of insider trading that I wr=
ite about are dumb. There are two possible interpretations of this fact:</p=
>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Most insider trading is dumb. Insider=
 trading is a fairly easy crime to catch, so it is dumb to do it, so if you=
 are doing it you will probably also do it in a dumb way.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some (much? most?) insider trading is smart, but o=
nly the dumb insider trading is=C2=A0<em>caught</em>. Lots of people are ou=
t there doing insider trading with clever tradecraft and <em>not </em>getti=
ng caught, which is why I am not writing about them.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think either interpretation is entirely plau=
sible; I lean toward Option 1 but I have little evidence for that.<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here are a <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32862759.260423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZX=
dzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0yMDQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB97aeafdd" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> US Securities and Exchange Commission enforcement action</a> and a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32862759.260423/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL2Zvcm1lci1lbXBsb3llZS10d28tbGVhZG=
luZy1nbG9iYWwtZmluYW5jaWFsLWluc3RpdHV0aW9ucy1hbmQtaGlzLWFzc29jaWF0ZXMtY2hhc=
mdlZA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB67c6ed87" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Justice Department crim=
inal case</a>=C2=A0against some guys who, allegedly, did mostly pretty good=
 insider trading? And yet not good enough?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission today a=
nnounced charges against Anthony Viggiano, a former analyst at a major inve=
stment firm and later at an international investment bank, and Christopher =
Salamone, Stephen A. Forlano, and Nathan Bleckley, for insider trading in a=
dvance of numerous merger and acquisition transactions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, in c=
onnection with his work at two financial institutions, Viggiano learned abo=
ut impending merger and acquisition transactions and strategic partnerships=
 before they were publicly announced. Viggiano, a resident of Baldwin, New =
York, allegedly obtained material nonpublic information about eight such tr=
ansactions and tipped his friend Salamone, who grew up on the same block an=
d whom he has known for approximately 20 years, about at least six of them.=
 Salamone, a resident of Long Beach, New York, allegedly traded in advance =
of the six transactions, resulting in proceeds of approximately $322,000. S=
alamone allegedly agreed to share his trading proceeds with Viggiano becaus=
e Viggiano=E2=80=99s own employer prohibited him from engaging in such trad=
es. The complaint further alleges that Viggiano tipped his close college fr=
iend Forlano about at least four transactions and that Forlano made approxi=
mately $113,000 in illegal profits trading in advance of three of those tra=
nsactions. Forlano, a resident of Tampa, Florida, also allegedly tipped oth=
er individuals, including his close, college friend Bleckley, a resident of=
 Altus, Oklahoma, who traded in advance of two transactions, resulting in i=
llegal gains of almost $25,000.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The case originated from the SEC Market Abuse =
Unit=E2=80=99s Analysis and Detection Center, which uses data analysis tool=
s to detect suspicious trading patterns.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The investment firm was Blackstone Inc. and th=
e bank <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32862759.26=
0423/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzLmJsb29tYmVyZ2xhdy5jb20vd2hpdGUtY29sbGFyLWFuZC1jcmltaW=
5hbC1sYXcvZXgtZ29sZG1hbi1hc3NvY2lhdGUtY2hhcmdlZC13aXRoLWluc2lkZXItdHJhZGluZ=
y1ieS11cw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBedcea03c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  was Goldman Sachs Gr=
oup Inc</a>. But the last sentence in that quote is the important one: The =
SEC can do data analysis to basically be like =E2=80=9Cthis one guy has had=
 a run of lucky trades on merger targets, let=E2=80=99s see what advisers w=
orked on all of those deals, and which employees of those advisers grew up =
on the same block as the guy who traded.=E2=80=9D A run of successful trade=
s on deals is enough to trigger the SEC=E2=80=99s suspicions, and then they=
 can figure out your connections to those deals.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But, as these things go, Viggiano and Salamone=
 seem to have insider traded in the basically smart way?=C2=A0The allegatio=
n is that Viggiano (the investment banker) got the inside information and S=
alamone traded on it: The insider did no trading and the trader had no obvi=
ous connection to inside information. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/32862759.260423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9=
saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb21wLXByMjAyMy0yMDQtMS5wZGY/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB98c2a85d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;"> SEC complaint</a> does not quote any incr=
iminating emails or text messages between them, or any suspiciously timed p=
hone calls, because there weren=E2=80=99t any:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In late 2022, Viggiano and Salamon=
e agreed to be more careful to not leave a trail of their communications re=
lating to their trading in Salamone=E2=80=99s brokerage accounts. Going for=
ward, they would communicate in person or using SIGNAL. Viggiano told Salam=
one to download SIGNAL for future communications so no one could read their=
 messages and their messages would not be preserved. Viggiano set the conve=
rsation rules in SIGNAL so that chats would expire five-minutes after they =
ended.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Good thing the SEC is <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32862759.260423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMjcvY2l0YWRlbC1taWdodC1maWdodC1mb=
3ItaXRzLXRleHRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjgyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwm=
dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXl=
zdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf1e654a0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  cracking down on unaut=
horized messaging apps</a> at investment banks!=C2=A0They split the profits=
 in the traditional way, with bags of cash:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On January 4, 2023, Salamone trans=
ferred $80,000 of the illegal trading proceeds from his brokerage account t=
o his bank account; the same day, he withdrew $20,000 in cash from his bank=
 account. He then hand-delivered the $20,000 in cash to Viggiano. Salamone =
subsequently delivered another $15,000 in cash to Viggiano over the course =
of two or three deliveries. Salamone intended to give Viggiano more cash, s=
ince their agreement called for a 50- 50 split of their trading profits, bu=
t Viggiano told Salamone to leave the profits in Salamone=E2=80=99s brokera=
ge account for future trades.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, while their trading was suspicious enough=
 to raise flags at the SEC, they did take steps to make it less suspicious:=
</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For some of their trades, Viggiano=
 instructed Salamone to buy multiple stocks, often in the same sector, in o=
rder to provide a =E2=80=9Csmokescreen=E2=80=9D narrative in case they were=
 questioned about their trading. For example, when they purchased MAXR secu=
rities, they also purchased securities in four other defense-related compan=
ies so they could say they were buying defense stocks in anticipation of a =
possible =E2=80=9CWorld War III.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nonetheless, they were caught.=C2=A0I suppose =
part of the problem for them is that the SEC=E2=80=99s methods of analysis =
are strong enough to catch them even without incriminating text messages. A=
nother part of the problem, though, is that they widened the circle to peop=
le who were less rigorous about tradecraft.=C2=A0Viggiano also allegedly ti=
pped his other friend Forlano, who then tipped=C2=A0<em>his=C2=A0</em>frien=
d Bleckley, and=C2=A0<em>they=C2=A0</em>did all sorts of dumb texting that =
the SEC quotes:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On July 9, 2021, Forlano told Bleckley via tex=
t message that he should buy AIG stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bleckley did not purchase AIG stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On July 14, 2021, the day the AIG Deal was ann=
ounced, Forlano and Bleckley had the following text message exchange:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=A2 Forlano: =E2=80=9Caig boom,=E2=80=9D=
 =E2=80=9Cdid u buy in??=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=A2 Bleckley: =E2=80=9CNah . . . not on =
AIG just Bc my funds are low,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CGreat call sorry I wasted i=
t.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=A2 Forlano: =E2=80=9Cbroooo I didnt wan=
na leave a trail but rigatoni literally works for [IF].=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CRigatoni=E2=80=9D was a nickname for =
Viggiano, and =E2=80=9C[IF]=E2=80=9D meant the Investment Firm where Viggia=
no worked.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bleckley responded to Forlano by text message:=
 =E2=80=9CBro You know the f[**]king code dont u=E2=80=9D; =E2=80=9CIf you =
say =E2=80=98mallard of all mallards=E2=80=99 I know fire away with everyth=
ing I got,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CF[**]k u should=E2=80=99ve told me f[**]k =
the feds.=E2=80=9D Forlano =E2=80=9Cloved=E2=80=9D Bleckely=E2=80=99s text =
about mallards;=C2=A0mallard or duck was their shorthand for a sure thing.<=
/p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have a secret insider trading code for =
your text messages, don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>explain the code in the text mes=
sages</em>, come on.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway though the FBI eventually did come call=
ing. Viggiano was not worried:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or around June 27, 2023=E2=80=
=94after the trading by Salamone based on material=C2=A0nonpublic informati=
on from Viggiano, alleged below=E2=80=94Viggiano told Salamone that he had =
been approached by law enforcement. Viggiano told Salamone not to worry, be=
cause they had traded the right way using =E2=80=9Csmokescreens=E2=80=9D to=
 avoid detection. In addition, they had been communicating about trading us=
ing SIGNAL, an application that Viggiano said would prevent others from rea=
ding their messages.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But he should have been, because=C2=A0Salamone=
 started recording their conversations for law enforcement<a class=3D"footn=
ote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important=
; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Agents from the Federal Bureau of Investigatio=
n interviewed ANTHONY VIGGIANO, the defendant, and Salamone in or about Jun=
e 2023. After those interviews, VIGGIANO made the following statements to S=
alamone that, unbeknownst to VIGGIANO, was recorded by Salamone:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">VIGGIANO: You have both the people here who ex=
ecuted trades, you have all that. What you're missing is the dots. Right? T=
hey have - they have me at [Firm-2] having access to this information, and =
the over here is ... trading that loosely connects to me. It doesn't take a=
 brain surgeon. So, what - what's more valuable? If I were to flip, or if S=
teve [Forlano Jr.] flipped. If Steve flipped, it's a he-said, she-said. Bec=
ause if - it was right now. If I flip, this whole thing's done, this case i=
s closed, and they're like, yeah.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">***<br />Salamone: =E2=80=A6=C2=A0You're givin=
g information to Steve [Forlano Jr.]?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">VIGGIANO: Nah. Nah. Because similar to you . .=
. signal, or like XBOX 360 chat, there's no tracing that. Good luck ever fi=
nding that. So, I mean, at worst - we're talking worst-case scenario, maybe=
 I said something in . ... like the very first one. But that's the worst ca=
se.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not the worst case!</p>
