<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have been accused of something terrible=
, your first reaction might be to call a lawyer. You will speak candidly to=
 the lawyer about your situation, and she will discuss it with you, and the=
n either she will be your lawyer or she won=E2=80=99t. If she becomes your =
lawyer =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you want to hire her and she agrees to work for yo=
u =E2=80=94=C2=A0then she will have a professional obligation to keep your =
secrets and not gossip about you to the press. If she does=C2=A0<em>not=C2=
=A0</em>become your lawyer =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you decide not to hire her, or=
 if you offer to but she turns you down =E2=80=94=C2=A0she will=C2=A0<em>al=
so=C2=A0</em>have a professional obligation to keep the secrets that you to=
ld her in your initial consultation.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#fo=
otnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none=
 !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bloc=
k;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have been accused of a certain sort of =
terrible thing, and you are a certain sort of person, your second reaction =
might be to call a corporate intelligence firm to dig up dirt on your accus=
ers. You will speak candidly to the corporate intelligence guy, and he will=
 discuss the case with you, and then either he will be your dirt-digger or =
he won=E2=80=99t. I do not know the ethical rules that apply to corporate i=
ntelligence firms! But apparently, when <em>they </em>end up <em>not </em>t=
aking=C2=A0a case, they are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/32862759.260423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjMtMDktMjcvY3Jpc3Bpbi1vZGV5LWpva2VkLWFib3V0LWFjY3VzZXJzLWJsYW1lZC13=
b2tlLWJyaWdhZGUtZm9yLWRvd25mYWxsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjgyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9=
tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyOCZ1dG1fY2=
FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4a91fc4c" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  happy=
 to talk to the press about it</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Crispin Odey approached a private investigator=
 who had done work for disgraced movie producer Harvey Weinstein to discuss=
 the =E2=80=9Cmassive witch hunt=E2=80=9D he faced after fresh claims of se=
xual misconduct.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHarvey had access to a lot of so much=
 more attractive girls, I have to tell you,=E2=80=9D Odey joked during the =
17-minute phone call. =E2=80=9CIf you lose an arm, you only get ten grand =
=E2=80=94 you know, if someone touches you on the bottom you might be able =
to get a hundred grand,=E2=80=9D he said elsewhere in the call.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The financier was speaking in late June to Set=
h Freedman, who runs London-based corporate intelligence firm Red Mist. The=
 pair ultimately didn=E2=80=99t work together, and Freedman shared his reco=
rding of the call with Bloomberg News, saying it was important that the pub=
lic hears Odey=E2=80=99s thinking about the situation at the time.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Okay! What is your model of Freedman=E2=80=99s=
 thinking here? Like, I feel like if you run a corporate intelligence firm,=
 a=C2=A0<em>certain amount=C2=A0</em>of your business is going to come from=
 people who, uh, are not afraid to say and also possibly do some monstrous =
stuff. (Freedman worked for Harvey Weinstein!) If you record them saying mo=
nstrous stuff and release the juiciest stuff to the press, won=E2=80=99t yo=
u lose a lot of business? Future lucrative monsters, reasonably, won=E2=80=
=99t trust you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose you could consciously choose that ap=
proach to distinguish yourself as, like, a Good corporate intelligence firm=
, one that vets its clients and only works for good innocent upstanding one=
s who do not say monstrous things in their initial consultations. (But, aga=
in: Weinstein!) Ostentatiously turning down (and turning on) some clients m=
ight make you more attractive to others.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or, also, I mean, I don=E2=80=99t know=C2=A0<e=
m>why=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=9Cthe pair ultimately didn=E2=80=99t work together,=
=E2=80=9D and I suppose an approach like =E2=80=9Cif you don=E2=80=99t hire=
 me I will leak your secrets to the press=E2=80=9D has some advantages. Als=
o it does demonstrate the ruthlessness that one wants in a corporate intell=
igence investigator.</p>
